\pop[-1]So your name is \N[1]! It is a pleasure for me to introduce you to
the world of Pokémon, \N[1].
\pop[-1]First of all, I'd like to explain about the Zero project, a new
method to develop as a Pokémon trainer, created by Professor Gary.
\pop[-1]Unlike the traditional method, in Heyday Island trainers don't
get eight medals and try to become the Champions of the region.
\pop[-1]Instead, they deal with different situations with their
Pokémon, power up their abilities, and prepare for big challenges.
\pop[-1]Not every person who is given a Pokémon has to use them to
battle, you must find your place in this vast world.
\pop[-1]Also, the Zero Project doesn't give you three options
for your first Pokémon as we used to do, and that's why I'm here.
encuesta

\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>Okay, \N[1]. Let's start with my presentation.
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>As you may know my name is Samuel Oak, and I study Pokémon.
I am also a good friend of Professor Ivy, the one who asked me to do this.
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>You may have a lot of questions. Let me explain you what I am
exactly doing here.
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>The classic method for a trainer to start with their adventure
is to choose one of three Pokémon that the professor of the region offers them.
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>Charmander, Squirtle and Bulbasaur in my case in Kanto.
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>However, recent studies have demonstrated that people get on
better with some Pokémon specie than others, deppending on the trainers and the
Pokémon personalities.
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>And that's why I am here. I am going to ask you some questions.
Then, I will send your answers to Professor Ivy, and by the time you arrive to
Heyday Island, she will have your Pokémon ready.
encuesta

\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>Well, if that happens I'm sorry but you won't be able to change it.

What is Heyday Island?
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>Good question. Heydey Island is an island where new trainers
follow this alternative method just like you. There are no gyms and no Pokémon
league there. It is a place where you can train, relax, have fun...
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>There are a lot of things to do there. You can just discover
what do you like the most, battles, contests, or other Pokémon activities.
Then you can visit Kanto, Johto and the rest when you feel ready.
\n<\C[2]Professor Oak>We don't want to tell the trainers what do they have to do.
This is what we call the \C[2]Zenith Method\C[0].
encuesta
